{
  "doc_id": "36003",
  "text": "The interpretation panel contains a number of scientific words and this, coupled with inadequate explanation of the weathering system, results in the current information not being comprehendible to a wide variety of tourists, considering their potential range in age, education, experience and cultural origin. [CITATION_1] has discussed the importance of making geological information accessible to the general public and the need to accommodate a diverse tourist profile. He reiterates that it is important to avoid scientific terms and to simplify the vocabulary and to demystify counterintuitive concepts in geology.",
